  "prompt": "What is the salary of an assistant in CSS after 7th pay commission?",
  "response": "As of the 7th Pay Commission in India, the salary of an Assistant in the Central Secretariat Service (CSS) typically falls under the pay level 7 or level 8, depending on the specific position and seniority. \n\n1. **Level 7**: The basic pay ranges from approximately \u20b944,900 to \u20b91,42,400 (in the pay matrix).\n2. **Level 8**: The basic pay ranges from approximately \u20b947,600 to \u20b91,51,100 (in the pay matrix).\n\nIn addition to the basic pay, there are various allowances such as Dearness Allowance (DA), House Rent Allowance (HRA), and others, which can significantly increase the overall salary.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's recommended to refer to official government notifications or the Ministry of Finance's guidelines regarding pay scales and allowances.",
